text: Veazie is an unincorporated community in King County, in the U.S. state of Washington. ==History== A post office called Veazie was established in 1890, and remained in operation until 1892. The community was named after Thomas Veazie, a businessperson in the logging industry. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in King County, Washington Category:Unincorporated communities in Washington (state)
title: Veazie, Washington
